# ── The duplicate that broke the deploy ────────────────
# `natan-portfolio/` is a byte-identical copy of this site WITH ITS OWN
# .git. Git recorded it as a gitlink (mode 160000) pointing at a commit
# in a repo it has no URL for, so every clone dies on submodule
# checkout — which is exactly what Netlify hit.
# 167MB, and none of it is needed: this folder is the real site.
natan-portfolio/

# ── Reference material — MUST NOT be published ─────────
# Full-page screenshots of another studio's site, kept locally as a
# design reference. Publishing them would host a competitor's pages on
# Natan's own commercial domain: a copyright exposure, and proof from
# his own server that he copied them. 78MB of pure downside.
A site to emulate/

# ── Superseded originals ───────────────────────────────
# Everything here was compressed into assets-opt/ (46MB -> 3.2MB).
# Only two files are still referenced by the live pages, so the rest is
# dead weight that would ship on every deploy.
assets/renders/
assets/websites/
assets/photo.png
# 1.5MB source portrait — only the compressed webp avatars ship
assets/PROFAIL.png
assets/resume.pdf

# ── Working screenshots dropped in the project root ────
# Raw full-page captures of client sites and AI-generated mockup source
# images, saved here while building. ~50MB, and none of it is linked
# from a page: what ships is the compressed copy under assets-opt/.
# Scoped to the root with a leading slash so the real artwork in
# assets/ and assets-opt/ is never caught by this.
/*.png
/*.jpg
/*.jpeg
/*.webp

# ── Superseded case screenshots ────────────────────────
# Per-project captures from an earlier version of the case page. The
# page now scrolls the full-page shot stored in Supabase instead, so
# these 3.2MB are no longer referenced by any page.
assets-opt/cases/

# ── Local noise ────────────────────────────────────────
desktop.ini
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
*.log
